### Signup a new user
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Login to get JWT token
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Connect to WebSocket

# To test the WebSocket connection, you can use a tool like Postman or a simple Node.js script.

# 1. Get the JWT token from the login request above.
# 2. Use a WebSocket client to connect to ws://localhost:3000.
# 3. When connecting, pass the token in the `auth` payload like this:
#    {
#      "token": "YOUR_JWT_TOKEN"
#    }

# You should see a log in the server console indicating that a user has connected.
